I have seen and written code in the form of C code and sed scripts that
use the non-digit first character test for a host name over a number.

I agree that the requirement of a non-digit character for a host name
should have never been there and the requirement for everyone to support
host names as long as 256 characters should be there....but that is the
breaks...it is real late in the game.

-Rudy

